Inter-Korean Workers Meeting Vows to Spearhead Patriotic Movement for Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- A joint press release was published at the meeting of representatives of workers in the north and south of Korea for implementing the June 15 joint declaration in Kaesong on Tuesday. 
 According to it, a meeting of representatives of workers of the north and the south for implementing the June 15 joint declaration was held by the Workers' Sub-Committee of the North Side's Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration and the Workers Headquarters of the South Side's Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration in Kaesong on March 14, 2006. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting the organizations of workers of the north and the south vowed to take the lead in the patriotic movement for reunification to achieve national independence, peace and the great national unity by the concerted efforts of the Koreans in the basic spirit of the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They agreed to increase their role so as to develop the June 15 Joint National Committee into a nationwide solidarity organization for the reunification movement both in name and reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also agreed to boost solidarity and cooperation among them as required by the June 15 era of reunification and have all contacts and functions in the direction of bringing about a new phase of national reunification this year.

March Issue of Newspaper "The Juche Idea" Published 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- The National Liaison Council of the Japan Society for the Study of Kim Jong Il's Works brought out the March issue of its newspaper "The Juche Idea".
 The newspaper carried a photo-accompanied account of an "Okinawa meeting to advance guided by Juche idea." It also quoted an honorary professor of Okinawa University as asserting at the meeting that the people of Okinawa should decide the fate of Okinawa and to this end they should achieve independence of Japan, guided by the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Carrying a report about the visit of a Japanese delegation for the study of the Juche idea to the DPRK on the occasion of the February holiday and a photo-accompanied account of the DPRK-Japan inter-governmental talks, the newspaper urged the Japanese government not to read the face of the U.S. but opt for normalizing the relations with the DPRK as early as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also carried a photo-accompanied account of a conference of the Japanese Society for the Study of Kimilsungism held in Okinawa.

Anniversary of Arboretum of KMP Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- The Arboretum of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace observed its 10th anniversary.
 The arboretum was established on March 13, Juche 85 (1996) in accordance with the noble intention of leader Kim Jong Il to build the palace where President Kim Il Sung lies in state as the supreme temple of Juche and the unanimous desire of all people.
 Over the last decade servicepersons of the People's Army and working people and schoolchildren from different parts of the country have planted and tended with care tens of thousands of tall trees, flowers and shrubs of hundreds of good species in the vast area around the palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The arboretum is home to a variety of rare trees, flowers and shrubs sent to it by different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting to mark the 10th anniversary of the arboretum took place on Mar. 13.
 Pak Song Nam, minister of Land and Environment Preservation, said in a report that  Kim Jong Il, after unrolling a new history of the cause of perpetuating the memory of the President, initiated the building of the arboretum suited to the nature of the supreme temple of Juche, personally chose its site and wisely led the construction project. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called on all officials and other working people to keep the arboretum in better shape and bring a fresh turn in the work to turn the whole country into a thick woodland and greenery.

U.S. Warhawks' Anti-DPRK Malarkey under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- The commander of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces in south Korea at a hearing of the U.S. Senate Armed Services Committee some time ago blustered that the military capacity of the DPRK poses a constant threat to the security of south Korea and other U.S. allies and Northeast Asia, talking about "nuclear program" and "conventional weapons."
 Dismissing this as shameless sophism to justify the military occupation of south Korea by the U.S. forces and its moves to provoke a war of aggression against the north, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Tuesday brands this as an intolerable provocation against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are past masters in fabricating lies to launch military invasion of other countries and nations, he notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At this very moment the U.S. imperialist warhawks are raising a frantic racket over military threat from the DPRK after deliberately throwing a hurdle in the way of the six-party talks for settling the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. by faking up a fictitious "counterfeit note issue" of the north. They openly announced that they would stage RSOI and Foal Eagle exercises, a replica of "Team Spirit" joint military exercises, which are a test nuclear war for the invasion of the north, from March 25, thus gravely threatening the Koreans desirous of peace and reunification.
 The outcries over "military threat" from the north raised by the U.S. imperialists are nothing but a doctrine of a war against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. imperialist warhawks venture a war on this land, the Korean army and people will fully exercise the deterrent for self-defense they have built under the banner of Songun and give vent to their enmity toward the U.S. so as to sternly punish the aggressors.

Spring Tree-Planting at Full Swing
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- The spring tree-planting is at full swing in the DPRK.
 The Ministry of Land and Environment Conservation has worked out an ambitious plan for the month of spring tree-planting and is dynamically pushing ahead with it.
 In response to the instructions of Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il that the servicepersons should stand in the van of covering the whole country with forests and gardens, they are planting and tending a lot of saplings of good species in the barrack compounds and stationing places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working people have turned out in the spring tree-planting campaign with a high degree of patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Sukchon County of South Phyongan Province, Anbyon County of Kangwon Province, Jongphyong County of South Hamgyong Province and all other cities and counties of the country, people of all strata are exerting efforts to creating forests of fiber-bearing, firewood, oil-bearing and fruit-bearing trees suitable to the climate of their areas.
 The campaign is being conducted with main emphasis on creating forests and gardens in the revolutionary sites and areas along highways and around industrial establishments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Each city and county in the country has newly arranged 20-60 hectares of nursery fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Yonthan County, North Hwanghae Province honored with the "model county in the protection of land and environment", alone, more than 203,400 trees were planted on the very tree-planting day (March 2). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A campaign for creating youth forests and Children's Union forests is vigorously launched among schoolchildren and youth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 March and October have been set as months of tree-planting in the country.
 The recent years have witnessed many successes made in the creation of forests through the vigorous campaign for turning the whole country into forests and gardens.
 Trees of good species including pine-nut, larch, acacia, Evodia Daniellii Benn and large chest-nut trees were planted in over 100,000 hectares of areas throughout the country last year.

Powerful Assistance to Countryside
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- A brisk campaign for rendering assistance to the countryside is being conducted in the DPRK.
 The ministries and national institutions stand in the van of the campaign in response to the joint New Year editorial calling for mobilizing and concentrating all the efforts to agriculture. They have sent a lot of farming materials including some 1,200 pieces in 28 kinds of tractor accessories and 79,900-odd pieces in 20 kinds of medium and small-sized farming implements and more than 24,400 tons of manure to rural communities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of the Ministry of Food Procurement and Administration went out to the Sinhung Co-op Farm in Jungsan County, South Phyongan Province, and dug up over 1,000 tons of peat to carpet fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And those of the Ministry of Post and Telecommunications and the Ministry of Machine-Building Industries acquainted themselves with farming preparations in relevant farms and provided them with the materials needed. 
 Cities and counties of North Phyongan Province, who had already carried more than 955,000 tons of compost to co-op farms, have continued to help farmers increase fertility of paddy and non-paddy fields in the province with the resolution to yield a bumper crop this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cities, counties and industrial establishments in North Hamgyong Province have tapped the inner reserves to render assistance, moral and material, to the countryside. People in Musan County sent the farming materials including over 20 kinds of medium and small-sized farming implements to farms, energetically inspiring agricultural working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people in Sariwon City, North Hwanghae Province, have provided several ten- thousand tons of compost and 12,000-odd pieces of farming implements to various co-op farms. Working people in Jagang Province and other provinces are all out in a similar campaign.

KCNA Discloses True Colors of Japan's Distortion of History
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- Japan has decided to use the "new history textbook" from 2006. Compiled in the textbook is a great part of the Korean history extremely distorted by reptile historians in the past.
 As already known, the Japanese imperialists who illegally occupied Korea in the early 20th century unscrupulously distorted the Korean history in an attempt to justify their colonial domination and obliterate the national spirit of the Korean people.
 Typical of the distortion are the reactionary doctrines on "four vassal regions under the Han Dynasty" and "Mimana Miyake" claiming that Korea had been subjected to other countries historically. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wudi, king of the Han Dynasty, that is, ruined Kojoson (ancient Korea) in 108 B.C., built Rakrang region, one of the four tributary regions under the Han Dynasty in the northwestern area of Korea around Pyongyang and "Mimana Miyake", a ruling machinery of the "Yamato Dynasty" of Japan, governed the area south of the River Han for several hundreds of years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such sophism of reptile historians was disputed by the historical circles of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea after Korea's liberation.
 It is not on the Korean peninsula but in the Liaodong area that the "four vassal regions under the Han Dynasty" were built. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the "History of the Three Kingdoms--Koguryo, Paekje and Silla", 30,000 soldiers of Koguryo attacked Hyondo region of the Qin Dynasty in the year of 302 and captured and escorted more than 8,000 men to Pyongyang. The Koguryo army also defeated Rakrang region in Liaodong in 313 and 314 and routed even the Hyondo region to the Liaoxi area in 318 to seize the region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Mimana Miyake", which was mentioned only in "Nihonshoki" (old records of Japanese history), was not a colonial ruling organ of Japan set up in Kaya area of Korea but a provisional administrative organ of the Yamato State in a Korean lineage small state formed in the Kibi area of west Japan (the area of Okayama Prefecture), before a unified state was formed in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This time, however, Japan came out again with the doctrines, the falsity of which has long been brought to light, in an attempt to legalize its past aggression of Korea and its wild ambition to stage a comeback to Korea.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il's work "On Having Correct Understanding of Nationalism" is a programmatic work which indicates a clear way for all the countries and nations to frustrate maneuvers of the imperialists for national obliteration and estrangement among nations and defend national independence, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article today.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 True nationalism is immediately patriotism today when people live and shape their destiny with their national states as units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nationalism is an idea of national independence for defending the sovereignty of the country and the nation from the aggressive moves of the U.S. imperialists. 
 Now the U.S. imperialists are resorting to crafty tactics to arrest the independent development of nations and achieve their ambition for domination. They claim that the idea of building an independent national state and patriotism are �gnational prejudice behind the times�h and "globalization" and "integration" are the trend of the times under the present-day condition where science and technology are making fast progress and economic exchanges among countries are brisk on the global scale. Preposterous is the cry for the �gintegration�h of the world involving politics, economy, ideology and culture today when each country and each nation are shaping their destinies with their own idea, system and culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nationalism is a patriotic idea of achieving the prosperity of the nation by its own efforts, opposing dependence on foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are presenting a distorted picture of the realities, claiming that they are bringing economic revival to different countries and nations with what they call "prescription�h and "aid". The "prescription" they are advertising is not a "panacea" for the rejuvenation of other's national economy and promotion of national reconciliation but a camouflage for covering up their aggressive and depredatory nature. 
 Everyone should be a true nationalist before being a revolutionary and there is no revolutionary away from his nation. This is the Juche-oriented view of nation of Kim Jong Il, concludes the article.

Rodong Sinmun on Three Charters of National Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- "Let us firmly stand by the three charters for national reunification, and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country by dint of the concerted efforts of the whole nation!" laid down in the joint slogans issued by the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the WPK represents the revolutionary faith and will of the Party and the Korean people to successfully realize the behests of President Kim Il Sung on national reunification, says Rodong Sinmun in an article Tuesday.
 The author of the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three principles of national reunification, the ten-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo put forward by Kim Il Sung are an immortal programme of reunification which the Korean nation should implement up to the hilt in accomplishing the cause of national reunification as they are the three charters for national reunification which give an integral systemization and consummation of the basic principles and ways of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three charters for national reunification are run through with the spirit of national independence regarding the nation's sovereignty and dignity as its life and soul. The basic idea and the hard core of the three charters are the spirit of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They indicate the most fair and reasonable way of achieving the reunification of the country at the earliest date possible in conformity with the realistic conditions of Korea in which  differing ideas and systems have existed for a long time in the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stipulate that Korea should be reunified in the manner of founding a national reunified state by the formula of federation based on one nation and one state, two systems and two governments, proceeding from the urgent demand of the nation and the realities of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il formulated the three principles of national reunification, the ten-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo as the three charters for national reunification, thus opening a broad avenue for the Korean nation to successfully accomplish the cause of national reunification, true to the behests of Kim Il Sung.

Poor Farce of Japanese Ultra-Right Conservatives Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- Recently the ultra-right conservatives of Japan called a meeting of the "special team for the solution to the abduction issue" at the prime minister's residence, at which they stressed the need to intensify information activities and get "support from the world" for the "settlement of the issue". They also called for publishing a booklet on the issue in different languages and distributing its copies among other countries. Then they arranged a press conference as regards the above-said meeting.
 Commenting on such row kicked up at the tacit connivance of the authorities and under their patronage, newspapers here today term it a despicable and poor charade staged as part of the U.S. anti-DPRK smear campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To repeat, like a parrot, just what the U.S. claims is an inveterate habit of the Japanese reactionary forces toeing the U.S. line, Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on:
 It is the height of folly for Japan to evade its responsibility to redress its crime-woven past by using the "abduction issue" as a smoke-screen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As far as the abduction issue is concerned, it is an important matter for which we should take Japan to task. Had Japan felt guilty even in the least of the hideous crimes it committed against humanity in the past, and had an iota of willingness to repent of them, it would not have dared to deny and embellish them. The relations between the DPRK and Japan have not yet improved but deteriorated due to the wrong behavior of Japan persistently evading the settlement of the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That is why Japan is censured as a politically and morally base country. If it persists in its efforts to evade the settlement of the past, it will stand further isolated internationally. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should be mindful of this and opt for liquidating its past at an early date.

Projected U.S.-South Korea Joint Military Exercises under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) --The south Korea-U.S. "Combined Forces Command" officially announced recently that it would stage large-scale joint military exercises from Mar. 25.
 Minju Joson Tuesday in a signed commentary terms the planned exercises premeditated criminal moves of the U.S. and the south Korean warhawks to push the situation on the Korean Peninsula to the brink of war and demands the U.S. roll back at once its plan to stage the war maneuvers to invade the DPRK.
 RSOI and Foal Eagle projected by the U.S. are nothing but a replica of "Team Spirit" joint military exercises, a dangerous test nuclear war against the DPRK, the news analyst observes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By staging the exercises this year, too, the U.S. and south Korean warmongers seek to escalate the tension on the peninsula and push it to the brink of war and thus deter the north-south relations from improving under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration and block the independent reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a serious attention is that the south Korean warmongers are chiming in with the U.S. scheme for the invasion of the DPRK. It is clear that this year, too, they seek to stand in military confrontation with the north through war exercises.
 This is well illustrated by their timing of the joint military exercises with the U.S. By planning to stage this saber rattling at a time when the 18th north-south ministerial talks were in the offing they glaringly revealed that they want neither dialogue nor reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities should behave with discretion, pondering over the grave consequences to be entailed by their involvement in the U.S. moves for a war of aggression against the DPRK.

KPA Panmunjom Mission Hits U.S.-S. Korea Joint Military Exercises
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- The Korean People's Army side makes it clear once again that it will never remain a passive onlooker to the U.S. preemptive attack on the DPRK. 
 A spokesman for the KPA Panmunjom Mission warned this in a statement issued on Tuesday to denounce the U.S. plan to stage large-scale RSOI and "Foal Eagle" joint military exercises involving huge U.S. and south Korean troops throughout south Korea from Mar. 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA side is of the view that a preemptive attack is not monopoly of the U.S. and the DPRK, too, has the right to preempt an attack as the most effective and positive act for self-defence in the light of the hard reality that the DPRK and the U.S. sides are still technically at war. It has already notified the UN of this stand.
 The U.S. redeployed its troops in and around the Korean Peninsula according to its new scenario for a war of aggression and perfected the operational plans through actual maneuvers. It has even "local eyewitnesses" who are ready to actively support and defend it in case it launches a war of aggression against the DPRK.
 We can not but take a serious note of the fact that the projected saber-rattling is timed to coincide with the racket the U.S. has kicked up to isolate and stifle the DPRK after spreading sheer lies about "counterfeit notes", "drug smuggling" and "human rights abuse" along with the fiction about the "proliferation of weapons of mass destruction" which it cited as a pretext for launching brigandish armed invasion of other countries. This behavior of the U.S. is a flagrant violation of the joint statement adopted at the six-party talks which stipulated that both sides shall solve issues on the principle of mutual respect and peaceful co-existence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No one can vouch that the RSOI and "Foal Eagle" to be staged involving huge troops and latest war means at a time when the distrust and confrontation between the DPRK and the U.S. are growing acute would not go over to an actual war.
 We are greatly enraged by the south Korean military authorities' decision to participate in the U.S-led exercises for a war of aggression against their fellow countrymen in gross breach of the June 15 spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA will follow with a high degree of vigilance the grave situation prevailing on the Korean Peninsula due to the projected war maneuvers and keep itself fully ready to go into action to cope with any event on its own initiative.
